Governor Abdullahi Ganduje of Kano State has ordered the State’s Anti-Corruption Commission to probe the claims by the Kano Zoological Gardens that a Gorilla in the state-owned Zoo swallowed N6.8 million. “The order was given on Friday and the commission has already swung into action,” a statement by the Chief Press Secretary to the Governor, Abba Anwar, said on Sunday in Kano. It quoted the Ganduje as directing the commission to look into the immediate and remote circumstances sorrounding the allegation and “unearth everything surrounding the incident”. The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN), reports that the animal was said to have swallowed N6.8m generated by the Zoo as gate fees collected from visitors of the garden, particularly during the Eid el- Fitr celebrations. (NAN) Kano zoo N6.8m: We will not hesitate to arrest gorilla if… – Police Ganduje threatens Kwankwaso with probe 5 MONTHS AFTER HANDOVER: Things fall apart between Kwankwaso and Ganduje Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin